  "instructions": [
    "Heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add sesame oil and let it melt into the pan. Add shallots, celery, garlic, and red peppers; stir for about 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Fold in pork tenderloin, tamari, vegetable broth, white pepper powder, and nutritional yeast (if using). Stir until meat is well coated with marinade.",
    "Cover and cook for 2-3 minutes. Add chopped nuts of your choice (such as cashews or almonds) to the pan and mix thoroughly.",
    "Cook uncovered for another minute. Remove from heat and serve hot over steamed rice or noodles."
